        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6097",
        "content": "Oh, how the roses riot in their bloom! The curtains stir as with an ancient pain; Her old piano gleams from out the gloom, And waits and waits her tender touch in vain.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
