        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6097",
        "content": "They're playing a tune in McGuffy's saloon, and it's cheery and bright in there (God! but I'm weak-since the bitter dawn, and never a bite of food); I'll just go over and slip inside-I mustn't give way to despair- Perhaps I can bum a little booze if the boys are feeling good.",
